## Skills Available (already downloaded — use these, don't create new ones)
- `frontend-design` — Production-grade UI, avoids generic AI aesthetic ← USE THIS ALWAYS
- `vercel-react-best-practices` — Next.js/Vercel optimization patterns (54 rule files)
- `tailwind-design-system` — Tailwind token system and patterns
- `web-design-guidelines` — General design principles
- `fullstack-developer` — Full-stack patterns when needed
- `systematic-debugging` — When something breaks, load this
- `subagent-driven-development` — For parallel work on multiple components
- `requesting-code-review` — Before finalizing any page component
- `brainstorming` — When planning new sections or features

## Agents Available (use these for specialized tasks)
- `explorer` — Map the codebase before touching anything (always run first)
- `planner` — Plan component architecture before coding
- `code-reviewer` — Review before marking any component done
- `security-auditor` — Before deploying to Vercel
- `test-writer` — After building each page

## Workflow for Building a Page
1. Run explorer agent: map existing components + conventions
2. Load relevant skill (frontend-design always, vercel-react-best-practices always)
3. Plan component structure — confirm with me before writing
4. Build mobile-first (375px → 768px → 1280px)
5. Run: `pnpm build && pnpm lint && npx tsc --noEmit`
6. Request code review via requesting-code-review skill

## Critical Rules for THIS Project
- ✅ Mobile-first responsive on every component
- ✅ Accessibility: semantic HTML, aria-labels on all interactive elements
- ✅ All project content stays true to the source — don't invent metrics
- ✅ Build completes with zero errors before calling anything done
- ❌ No dark navy/teal aesthetic — that's the AI-generated look we're replacing
- ❌ No Inter/Roboto/Arial — pick a font with personality
- ❌ No Lorem Ipsum — use the real content from prototype JSX
- ❌ No hardcoded colors — Tailwind classes or CSS custom properties only

## Environment Variables
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` — Full site URL (e.g. https://richardpillaca.com)
- No backend, no DB — this project has no secrets beyond the above

## Definition of Done (per page)
- [ ] Matches Figma design intent
- [ ] Renders correctly at 375px, 768px, 1280px
- [ ] `pnpm build` — zero errors
- [ ] `pnpm lint` — zero errors
- [ ] `npx tsc --noEmit` — zero errors
- [ ] All content is real (no placeholder text)
- [ ] Deployed to Vercel preview URL and visually checked